cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for image restoration using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves modifying the original restoration networks to generalize over a spectrum of degradation settings, which requires some level of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) expertise. The paper also presents experimental results on image inpainting, interpolation, and super-resolution, which are common tasks in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the proposed method involves a recursive module, which is a common technique in neural network optimization (cs.NE).
